    <accessrestrict id="aspace_hzc210972n506as61907989791255">
      <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
      <p>Use of original papers requires an appointment and is limited to the Archives' Washington, D.C., Research Center. Microfilmed materials must be consulted on microfilm. Contact Reference Services for more information.</p>
    </accessrestrict>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_hzc210972n520as06208160214680">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>Papers compiled by Sizer in preparation for THE AUTOBIOGRAPHY OF JOHN TRUMBULL, PATRIOT-ARTIST, 1756-1843 (Yale University Press, 1953) including correspondence, catalogs, clippings, books, magazines, pamphlets, typescripts of lectures and broadcasts, notes and working papers, photostats, photographs and pictorial reproductions.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <altformavail id="aspace_hzc210972n530as52315893211494">
      <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
      <p>35mm microfilm reels D172-D175 available at Archives of American Art offices and through interlibrary loan.</p>
    </altformavail>
    <relatedmaterial id="aspace_hzc210972n544as81016588720332">
      <head>Related Materials</head>
      <p>Sizer material on Trumbull paintings also located at Yale University.</p>
    </relatedmaterial>
    <bioghist id="aspace_hzc210972n545as88847960334338">
      <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
      <p>Art historian; New Haven, Conn. Trumbull was a New York City painter.</p>
    </bioghist>
